The forces of the giant strike are gathering.
The League Syndicates and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will form a strike committee on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last for indefinite time.
On Saturday, a protest meeting will be held, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - unemployment will be initiated.
With all certainty this action will cause great transport difficulties, since the railway traffic will be completely stopped and until 13 hours the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be in strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Syndicates will report on the details of their Monday strike that they will celebrate jointly with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
Also the strike committee of the LIGA and the National Machinery Syndicate will be formed to coordinate the actions of Monday.
On Saturday, a protest meeting will be held, as long as the participating trade unions will vote on Monday in strike for an indefinite time, if there is no agreement with the government.
This means, that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves the public health law, the trade unions will immediately withdraw their call to strike.
Instead, if the law is approved, the strike committees will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the Monday day order of the National Assembly it is also possible that only the public health law is voted in the very entering hours of the night, or near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant transport difficulties: on the railways it will stop working for indefinite time, in the morning it may stop a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the interurb bus transport of the Volán companies.
Simultaneously, in numerous points of the country will be closed half of the roads.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some trade unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Railway Workers’ Syndicate (SLTF) could not reach an agreement on the minimum services, though, by approaching Christmas holidays, more and more people travel on the trains.
According to information received so far, from the start of the day until 13 hours will be in strike the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, the Budapest Airports from 7 to 9 am, will celebrate a four-hour strike the LIGA Syndicates of the Electric and Thermal Energy Industry, the Educators Syndicates called for a 2-hour strike and the Democratic Syndicate of the Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will vote in national strike in alternative hours and the Democratic Syndicate of Workers of the Health and Social Sector (SDTSSS), which are part of the Syndical Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands formulated by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal regarding the reform of public health and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will enter into force next year.
The third is that they assure, even before 2010, for the case of advanced pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Railway Workers Syndicate (SLTF), which is part of the League Syndicates, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard increases the risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, from several points of view has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company’s “Risk Warning” it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk constitutes the fact that “with the aggravation of the ethnic tensions existing between the Gita and non-Gita population of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic confrontations may occur.”
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of a event of this character, the representative of the research institut added.
They stated that all this was due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: “the protagonists of public life ceded the public debate of the gitano problem to the representatives of the radical and extremist political groups, who were able to fundamentate their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between the gitans and the Hungarians.”
This worsenes the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts.
In addition to that, according to the Institute of Investigations, the activity of the National Guard, due to the great attention of the national and international media, “significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially as regards the stability and democratic development of the country.”
