What insurance is suitable for me?
The car insurance, which covers the driver before possible crashes, is an important expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, card age, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of this, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First we have to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange that it is responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in case of accident.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, age of the card, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is given to this, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of the statistics, so that at greater probability of suffering an accident, greater quota to pay.
It is for that reason that both the older 25 and women have to pay lower primes, as statistics reflect that they have a lower sinistrality index due to their prudence.
Also, taking hand of the accounts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of having some kind of percance.
As the frequency increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies take into account when setting the price of the premium.
It is therefore that the driver must study the situation well to choose that car insurance that best fits your profile.
We will expose the most significant variables here when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that this, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 find themselves with various inconveniences when hiring an insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the carnet age.
Although the ideal thing to be well insured is an all-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most precaved drivers can choose all-risk with franchise, so that they get the coverage of an insurance at all-risk but at a more factible price.
This type of agreement would imply that the customer pays a part of the amount of the sinister.
“The part of the amount of the accident that the customer provides will be pre-established based on the value of the prime, which will be higher as low the amount is,” said Luis Noguera, top responsible in Spain of First Europe, online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer is guaranteed protection against damages caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A counsel.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be careful and avoid crimes to the extent possible, as this will impact on the bonus, which can reduce the cost of the insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company possesses.
On the contrary, a penalty is a recharge on that basic fee.
“The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and the benefit of the company.
If the company has had a good year, it will be possible to increase the bonuses,” Noguera clarifies.
After the 25 year gap, drivers have it easier when hiring an insurance, since the sinistrality index is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended thing is to hire a whole risk with franchise.
“Normally young people can’t make use of the previously acquired experience when it comes to an accident, and even when driving,” the director in Spain of the European company says, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of driving, once passed the ‘fear of the novice’.
However, if the customer is married but still has no children it is preferable that he negotiates an insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation is permitted, of course.
Marriages with children are considered by the insurance companies as the public with a lower sinistrality index, so the recharges will be less.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with franchise (will be this of 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to allow the luxury of assuming a greater quantity of franchise,” Luis Noguera said.
For retirees it is recommended a risk insurance with franchise (as this is 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver before possible crimes, but also because it represents an important expenditure, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
