Data from a European spacecraft in orbit showed the planet more similar to a Earth twin than previously observed.
Venus is the closest planet to Earth.
The two planets have similar size and occupy similar orbits, although Venus is slightly closer to the Sun.
Millions of years ago, Venus could have had conditions similar to those that made the Earth a habitable planet, scientists now believe.
